## Getting started
1. Clone this repo
1. Run `cp .sample.env .env` to create an `.env` file. See [.sample.env](.sample.env) for keys.
1. Run `cp .sample.env.test .env.test` to create an `.env.test` file. See [.sample.env.test](.sample.env.test) for keys.
1. Create `master.key` or environment variable `RAILS_MASTER_KEY` in `.env` with the secret key.
1. Add bundle config for private gems `bundle config --local GITHUB__COM {GITHUB_AUTH_KEY}`. You can find this key from heroku pipeline under `BUNDLE_GITHUB__COM`
1. To edit credentials type `EDITOR='code --wait' rails:credentials:edit` in the termial. You can replace `EDITOR` with your own editor choice.

